Teaching Assistant (2023.9 - 2023.12)¶

🌟Course: STA103 Applied Statistics for Business and Economics¶

🌟Description:¶

Descriptive statistics; probability; random variables; expectation; binomial, normal, Poisson, other univariate distributions; joint distributions; sampling distributions, central limit theorem; properties of estimators; linear combinations of random variables; testing and estimation;

🌟Duty:¶

a. Facilitating Discussions: Leading discussions to encourage student engagement and critical thinking for statistical principle.

b. Offering Tutoring or Office Hours: Holding regular office hours to provide additional support and guidance to students.

c. Proctoring and Grading Exams: Assisting with exams desgin, proctoring and grading exams according to the guidelines.
